parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the leaf springs can cause the tires to rub against the frame of the vehicle, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate axle and spring rating can cause the leaf springs to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The tires rub against the frame of the vehicle
the leaf springs are fractured or broken
the vehicle feels unstable or sways while driving
the brakes are ineffective
the wheels are unevenly worn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes are ineffective
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pads are worn unevenly
the wheel bearings leak grease onto the brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Flex in RV Frames (Lippert Frames) Causing Structural Integrity Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive flex in the front section of the RV frame, particularly in the hitch/pinbox area, can lead to cracked frames, stress cracking in sidewalls, and seam separation at joints, causing potential safety hazards due to decreased structural integrity of the frame and structure. This can result in accidents or injuries on the highway.
symptoms: Cracked frames
stress cracking in sidewalls
seam separation at joints
water intrusion
floor-to-frame bolts pulling through the frame
interior trim not staying in place
front cap fiberglass spider webbing
and plastic edging on the roof pulling staples from the underlayment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Leaf Spring to Body Frame Weld Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the welds connecting the leaf springs to the body frame can cause the trailer to become unstable, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or even a rollover.
symptoms: The trailer suddenly becomes unstable or wobbles
the trailer leans to one side
the trailer's suspension makes unusual noises
the trailer's ride height changes
the trailer's axle or wheels become misaligned.
